<paragraph blockId="53.[192,1441,195,795]" pageId="53" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis box="[240,374,707,731]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="52">Etymology</emphasis>
—This species is named 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blahnik &amp; Holzenthal" authorityYear="2017" box="[693,840,707,731]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Mortoniella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="53" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flexuosa">
<emphasis box="[693,840,707,731]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="52">M. flexuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[1047,1165,707,731]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="52">flexuosus</emphasis>
, meaning winding or with many bends, and referring to the sinuously bent dorsolateral process of the inferior appendage in this species.
</paragraph>
